The paper deals with the problem of ensemble clustering of high-dimensional data, which is a common problem in machine learning and data mining. The paper proposes a novel approach that creates a large number of diversified metrics and subspaces to construct an ensemble of diversified base clusterings. This approach involves techniques such as randomization, similarity matrices, and entropy-based criteria. These techniques are commonly used in the fields of machine learning, artificial intelligence, data mining, computer vision, and social and information networks. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DM (Data Mining), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
